    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix missing break statements in E1AP bearer context management\n\n### Summary\nThe E1AP bearer context management code in the CU-UP was experiencing unexpected behavior during bearer context modification procedures. Investigation revealed that two DevAssert statements were using assignment operators (=) instead of comparison operators (==), causing unintended fallthrough behavior in switch statements.\n\nThis issue manifested as incorrect UP TNL information processing, where the code would not properly validate the presence of GTP tunnel parameters, leading to potential data corruption or incorrect bearer setup.\n\nThe root cause was identified in the extract_BEARER_CONTEXT_MODIFICATION_REQUEST function where critical validation checks were silently modifying data instead of performing comparisons.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/E1AP/e1ap.c`: Fixed incorrect assignment operator in DevAssert at line 1359\n- `openair2/E1AP/e1ap.c`: Fixed incorrect assignment operator in DevAssert at line 1387\n\n"
}